*mailwrapper-0.2.1 (15 Dec 2004)

  15 Dec 2004; Grant Goodyear <g2boojum@gentoo.org>
  +mailwrapper-0.2.1.ebuild:
  New version fixes up man pages to point to /etc/mail/mailer.conf instead
  of /etc/mailer.conf.  Leaving all keywords the same since the changes
  were only to the man pages.  Closes bug 53234.  Thanks to Nick Fisher
  and Luke Macken.

  28 Sep 2004; Andrej Kacian <ticho@gentoo.org> metadata.xml:
  Fixed herd name in metadata.xml.

*mailwrapper-0.2 (30 May 2004)

  30 May 2004; Grant Goodyear <g2boojum@gentoo.org> +files/mailer.conf,
  +mailwrapper-0.2.ebuild:
  New version that uses /etc/mail/mailer.conf.

  25 Apr 2004; Joshua Kinard <kumba@gentoo.org> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  Marked stable on mips.

  23 Apr 2004; Bryan Østergaard <kloeri@gentoo.org> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  Stable on alpha.

  23 Apr 2004; Travis Tilley <lv@gentoo.org> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  stable on amd64

  22 Apr 2004; Grant Goodyear <g2boojum@hotmail.com> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  Marking stable on x86.

  17 Apr 2004; Jason Wever <weeve@gentoo.org> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  Stable on sparc.

  01 Apr 2004; <randy@gentoo.org> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  Adding s390 keywords

  29 Mar 2004; Lars Weiler <pylon@gentoo.org> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  stable on ppc, as it is a dependency for net-mail/exim-4.24-r3

  18 Mar 2004; Grant Goodyear <g2boojum@hotmail.com> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  Adding additional ppc64, hppa, and ia64 keywords that broke ssmtp.

  18 Mar 2004; Jon Portnoy <avenj@gentoo.org> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild :
  AMD64 keywords.

  18 Mar 2004; Grant Goodyear <g2boojum@hotmail.com> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  Added ~alpha.  My sincere apologies for all of the archs I broke yesterday!

  18 Mar 2004; David Holm <dholm@gentoo.org> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  Added to ~ppc.

  18 Mar 2004; Joshua Kinard <kumba@gentoo.org> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  Added ~mips to KEYWORDS.

  17 Mar 2004; Jason Wever <weeve@gentoo.org> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  Added ~sparc keyword so you can now emerge ssmtp and postfix without it dying
  due to bad dependencies.

  17 Mar 2004; Grant Goodyear <g2boojum@hotmail.com> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  Updated the ebuild to remove the protection that had kept users
  from overwriting /usr/sbin/sendmail.  Now that we're gearing up to
  have all mtas install mailwrapper this protection is unwanted.

*mailwrapper-0.1 (08 Mar 2004)

  08 Mar 2004; Grant Goodyear <g2boojum@hotmail.com> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  New ebuild.

